      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mix the first dough (evening before)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "In the stand mixer bowl, combine the 250 g flour, yeast, sugar, and water. Mix on low with the dough hook for 2 minutes, then add the egg yolks."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Increase to medium and mix for 5 minutes until a smooth dough forms. Add the softened butter a few cubes at a time, waiting for each addition to be incorporated before adding more. The dough will become smooth, glossy, and slightly tacky."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cover the bowl and leave at room temperature (20 to 22°C) for 8 to 10 hours, or overnight."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Add the second dough (next day)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The first dough should have grown considerably and smell yeasty. Add the second dough ingredients in this order: flour, sugar, salt, then egg yolks one at a time, then vanilla and zest."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mix on medium for 10 minutes. The dough needs to reach the "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "windowpane test",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "term": "windowpane test",
                          "termId": "cmpbczyhi0001cgv4jawhdu8k"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": stretch a small piece thinly between your fingers; it should be translucent without tearing. This can take 15 to 20 minutes of mixing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Add butter and fruit"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the 120 g softened butter in small amounts, fully incorporating each addition. The dough will go loose and sticky, then gradually come back together."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Once all the butter is in, add the candied peel and raisins. Mix briefly on low to distribute."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Transfer to a lightly oiled bowl, cover, and leave at 22 to 26°C for 3 to 4 hours until doubled."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Shape and final proof"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Turn the dough out onto a very lightly oiled surface. Fold the edges into the centre, turn upside down, and roll gently to create surface tension."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Place seam-side down in the panettone mould. Cover loosely and prove at room temperature for 4 to 6 hours; the dough should rise just above the rim of the mould."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Score and bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Preheat the oven to 175°C conventional."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use a sharp blade or scissors to score a cross in the top of the dough. Place a small knob of butter in the centre of the cross; this opens the top and bastes it during baking."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Bake in the lower third of the oven for 40 to 45 minutes, until an internal probe reads 92 to 95°C and the top is deep golden brown. If the top colours too quickly, cover loosely with foil after 25 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cool upside down"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "As soon as the panettone comes from the oven, skewer it horizontally through the base with two knitting needles or long skewers."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Hang it upside down between two tall pots or across a roasting tin so the dome hangs free. The warm crumb is too fragile to support its own weight and will collapse if allowed to cool upright."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Leave to hang for at least 3 hours before turning upright."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Troubleshooting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Dough not passing windowpane test after 20 minutes: check the butter was fully softened, not melted. Cold butter stops the gluten from developing; melted butter saturates the network. Continue mixing in short bursts, resting 5 minutes between to cool the dough."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Very slow rise on the second proof: enriched doughs proof slowly at room temperature. Move the mould somewhere warmer (25 to 28°C) or extend the time. Rushing with heat above 30°C will melt the butter out of the dough."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Crumb collapsed on cooling right-side up: next time, hang inverted immediately. The structure does not set firmly until the crumb has cooled completely."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
